Label: Assay
Description: Unique identifier for an assay instance in the NASA Open Science Data Repository (OSDR)

Label: Anatomy
Description: UBERON ontology class name of an anatomical entity examined in an assay

Label: CellType
Description: Cell ontology (CL) class name of a cell type examined in an assay

Label: Gene
Description: Unique identifier for a human or model organism gene (ENTREZ id)

Label: Study
Description: Unique identifier for a study instance in the NASA Open Science Data Repository (OSDR)

Label: MethylationRegion
Description: Unique identifier for a 1,000 base pair genomic region (MethylationRegion) exhibiting differential methylation

Label: Mission
Description: Unique identifier for a mission instance in the NASA Open Science Data Repository (OSDR)

Label: CONDUCTED_MIcS
Description: Mission conducted study

Label: INVESTIGATED_ASiA
Description: Assay investigated anatomy

Label: INVESTIGATED_ASiCT
Description: Assay investigated cell type

Label: IS_ORTHOLOG_MGiG
Description: Model organism gene is an ortholog of a human gene

Label: MEASURED_DIFFERENTIAL_EXPRESSION_ASmMG
Description: Assay measured differential expressions of a model organism gene

Label: MEASURED_DIFFERENTIAL_METHYLATION_ASmMR
Description: Assay measured differential methylation in a methylation region

Label: METHYLATED_IN_MGmMR
Description: Model organism gene methylated in methylation region

Label: PERFORMED_SpAS
Description: Study performed assay

Label: adj_p_value
Description: Multiple testing-corrected p-value assessing the statistical significance of each gene's differential expression after controlling the false-discovery rate (FDR). Smaller values (e.g., <= 0.05) indicate that the observed log2 fold change is unlikely to arise by chance, even after accounting for the large number of simultaneous tests performed in the experiment. (float)

Label: chromosome
Description: Name or number of the chromosome (string)

Label: dist_to_feature
Description: Distance to feature (int)

Label: end
Description: Ending base pair position (int)

Label: end_date
Description: End date of mission (date)

Label: factor_space_1
Description: Primary experimental grouping for samples used the in assay, indicating whether it was exposed to Space Flight or maintained under control conditions: Ground Control, Basal Control, or Vivarium Control (string)

Label: factor_space_2
Description: Secondary experimental grouping for samples used in the assay, indicating whether it was exposed to Space Flight or maintained under control conditions: Ground Control, Basal Control, or Vivarium Control (string)

Label: factors_1
Description: Primary experimental factor(s) applied at the assay level (independent variables intentionally varied by the investigator); often corresponds to study-level design (e.g., Space Flight). Additional factors (e.g., dose, time point, sex, strain) may also be included. (string[])

Label: factors_2
Description: Secondary experimental factor(s) for this assay, typically the comparative group(s) in analysis connecting this assay to differential conditions (e.g., Ground Control). (string[])

Label: flight_program
Description: Type of flight program (string)

Label: in_exon
Description: Boolean flag indicating whether the methylation region overlaps with an exon (boolean)

Label: in_intron
Description: Boolean flag indicating whether the methylation region overlaps with an intron (boolean)

Label: in_promoter
Description: Boolean flag indicating whether the methylation region overlaps with a promoter region (boolean)

Label: log2fc
Description: Log2-transformed fold change in gene expression between the experimental condition and its reference baseline. Positive values indicate up-regulation (higher transcript abundance), while negative values denote down-regulation (lower transcript abundance) relative to the control. (float)

Label: material_1
Description: Biological material analyzed in the first assay group (e.g., tissue, cell type, organ) (string)

Label: material_2
Description: Biological material analyzed in the second assay group (e.g., tissue, cell type, organ) (string)

Label: material_id_1
Description: Controlled ontology identifier for the first material (e.g., UBERON code) (string)

Label: material_id_2
Description: Controlled ontology identifier for the second material (e.g., UBERON code) (string)

Label: material_name_1
Description: Preferred ontology-based name for the first material (e.g., UBERON term) (string)

Label: material_name_2
Description: Preferred ontology-based name for the second material (e.g., UBERON term) (string)

Label: measurement
Description: Type of data produced by the assay, describing the focus of the analysis (string)

Label: methylation_diff
Description: Percent change in methylation in base pair range (float)

Label: organism
Description: NCBI scientific organism name (string)

Label: project_title
Description: Title of project (string)

Label: project_type
Description: Type of project (string)

Label: q_value
Description: Adjusted p-value to control for false discovery rate (float)

Label: space_program
Description: Sponsor of the mission (string)

Label: start
Description: Starting base pair position (int)

Label: start_date
Description: Start date of mission (date)

Label: symbol
Description: Gene symbol for model organism (string)

Label: taxonomy
Description: NCBI taxonomy ID (string)

Label: technology
Description: Platform or method used to generate assay data (e.g., sequencing platform, mass spectrometry, imaging) (string)
